JOHANNESBURG - Ministers representing the coronavirus National Command Council in the economic cluster will update the nation on Friday. The rand has hit a new all-time low on Friday. READ: SA Lockdown: Informal food traders allowed to operate It's now 40 percent weaker to the US dollar compared to the same time last year. On Thursday, the NCC said informal food traders are now allowed to operate but they must get a permit. Previously, only spaza shops were allowed to trade during the 21-days lockdown.